<title type="html"><![CDATA[4/15 (Thu.) Happier Life or Live Longer? / Acquired Taste (Host: Sherry Liao)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=488&amp;p=510#p510"><![CDATA[
<span style="color: #FF0000">Place: 丹堤咖啡, 台北市延平南路107號2樓 (MRT 西門站4號出口)<br />Agenda:<br />07:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks <br />07:05-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />07:40-8:00 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation</span><br /><br />Session I: Happier Life or Live Longer?<br /> <br />A philosopher asks: Is a longer life a happier one?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://edition.cnn.com/2018/07/23/health/living-longer-philosophy-partner">https://edition.cnn.com/2018/07/23/heal ... hy-partner</a><!-- m --><br /> <br />Being happier will help you live longer, so learn how to be happier<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://edition.cnn.com/2019/09/30/health/happiness-live-longer-wellness">https://edition.cnn.com/2019/09/30/heal ... r-wellness</a><!-- m --><br /> <br />Questions:<br />1.      Do you think there is a ceiling on how long human beings can live?  Do you agree that there is a &quot;mortality plateau&quot; as mentioned in the first article?<br />2.      If possible, to what age do you wish to live?  Why?<br />3.      Do your goals and desires change at different stages of your life? What life goals do you think you would have if you can live very long?<br />4.      If you could wish for just one thing, would it be happiness or a long life?<br />5.      How do you obtain happiness?  In your opinion, what creates a sustained feeling of happiness?<br /> <br />Session II: Acquired Taste<br /> <br />An acquired taste? McDonald's China offers burger featuring Spam and crushed Oreos<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/mcdonalds-china-oreo-spam-burger-intl-hnk/index.html">https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/ ... index.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.      Do you think taste is innate or acquired?  If acquired, can you acquire a taste for anything?<br />2.      Do you love or hate the following foods: black coffee, blue cheese, sushi, dark chocolate, oysters, pickles, kimchi, liver, and cilantro?  Do you think they are simply good, truly bad, or actually an acquired taste?<br />3.      What kind of new foods have you tried recently?  What is the most bizarre food you have ever tried?  What is a food that you hated as a child but now love to eat?<br />4.      Do you love to try creative or exotic foods (say, Domino's bubble milk tea pizza), or do you have a distinctive fixation on food and just want your food to “taste good”? What type of food do you like most?<br />5.      How would you describe Taiwanese food culture?<br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">P.S.<br />1.因聚會地點是在咖啡店內，所以有低消80元喔。<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~</span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Fri Apr 09, 2021 11:33 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
